 user probably uses an external workflow with JDK21. I should ensure that existing tests in the worktree are run correctly. I need to think about setting the command line allowance properly before classpath definition and using System.getProperty(\\\"java.class.path\\\") to reference the current classpath.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating subprocess options**\\n\\nI'm considering the forked subprocess setup with `-javaagent` and `-Djava.security.manager=allow`, but I’m wondering if it should also include Gradle's test retry agent. My focus is on filtering specifically for `javaagent`. If JaCoCo isn't present, the tests might still pass, but I wouldn't get coverage data. However, the workflow is designed for coverage, so that's alright. Lastly, I’ll need the process output for debugging purposes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JavaTest execution**\\n\\nI'm thinking I don't need to avoid failures in JavaTest. I wonder if the external workflow could run natively without a classpath. Maybe inspecting in Native Image isn't possible. I’m considering using `ClassLoader.getSystemResource(\\\"org_mozilla/rhino/FunctionObjectTest.class\\\")`, but the resource might not be present in native. If the test classpath isn’t available as files for the fork, I could assert a public scenario without skipping the necessary checks. It seems like that’s a fallback capability, rather than a prohibition!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring classpath properties**\\n\\nI’m considering the native image context where `java.class.path` might still hold the original value. I wonder if I could read the class resource protocol “file” for `FunctionObjectTest.class`. There seems to be a possibility of using the classpath property if it's non-blank. It looks like I need to edit this aspect as I work through it. Let’s see how I can implement these changes effectively!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_pFQItRpeXzbKySUY1y3uJUO3|fc_05c25c4fd7dbb290016a27621e2cd48194a27c9ebed0104bfd", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/FunctionObjectTest.java", "limit": 240}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 847, "output": 1884, "cacheRead": 44544, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47275, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780965863428, "responseId": "resp_05c25c4fd7dbb290016a2761e855208194a993c7d9635db2dc"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_pFQItRpeXzbKySUY1y3uJUO3|fc_05c25c4fd7dbb290016a27621e2cd48194a27c9ebed0104bfd", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mozilla.rhino;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.ReflectPermission;\nimport java.security.Permission;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.Context;\nimport org.mozilla.javascript.ScriptableObject;\n\npublic class FunctionObjectTest {\n    @Test\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    void definesFunctionPropertiesWhenDeclaredMethodAccessIsDenied() {\n        Context context = Context.enter();\n        try {\n            ScriptableObject scope = (ScriptableObject) context.initStandardObjects();\n            SecurityManager previousSecurityManager = System.getSecurityManager();\n            boolean securityManagerInstalled = installReflectAccessDenyingSecurityManager(\n                    previousSecurityManager);\n            try {\n                scope.defineFunctionProperties(\n                        new String[] {\"fallbackGreeting\"},\n                        PublicFunctions.class,\n                        ScriptableObject.DONTENUM);\n            } finally {\n                if (securityManagerInstalled) {\n                    System.setSecurityManager(previousSecurityManager);\n                }\n            }\n\n            Object result = ScriptableObject.callMethod(\n                    context, scope, \"fallbackGreeting\", new Object[] {\"Rhino\"});\n            assertThat(Context.toString(result)).isEqualTo(\"hello Rhino\");\n        } finally {\n            Context.exit();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class PublicFunctions {\n        private PublicFunctions() {\n        }\n\n        public static String fallbackGreeting(String name) {\n            return \"hello \" + name;\n        }\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    private static boolean installReflectAccessDenyingSecurityManager(\n            SecurityManager previousSecurityManager) {\n        if (previousSecurityManager != null) {\n            return false;\n        }\n        try {\n            System.setSecurityManager(new DeclaredAccessDenyingSecurityManager());\n            return true;\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException | SecurityException exception) {\n            return false;\n        }\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"removal\")\n    private static final class DeclaredAccessDenyingSecurityManager extends SecurityManager {\n        @Override\n        public void checkPermission(Permission permission) {\n            denyDeclaredAccess(permission);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void checkPermission(Permission permission, Object context) {\n            denyDeclaredAccess(permission);\n        }\n\n        private void denyDeclaredAccess(Permission permission) {\n            if (permission instanceof ReflectPermission\n                    && \"suppressAccessChecks\".equals(permission.getName())) {\n                throw new SecurityException(permission.getName());\n            }\n            if (permission instanceof RuntimePermission\n                    && \"accessDeclaredMembers\".equals(permission.getName())) {\n                throw new SecurityException(permission.getName());\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780965918547}]}
